<subSubSection pageId="113" pageNumber="392" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="113.[2028,2623,1706,2133]" pageId="113" pageNumber="392">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1903" box="[2029,2267,1824,1857]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Peromyscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="113" pageNumber="392" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="beatae">Peromyscus beatae</taxonomicName>
1s in the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Baird" baseAuthorityYear="1855" box="[2440,2505,1824,1857]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Peromyscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="113" pageNumber="392" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="boylii">boylii</taxonomicName>
species group. After being described as a species, it was subsumed as a subspecies of P. boyli. More recent studies indicate that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1903" box="[2512,2623,1943,1976]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Peromyscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="113" pageNumber="392" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="beatae">P. beatae</taxonomicName>
is genetically distinct from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Baird" baseAuthorityYear="1855" box="[2443,2551,1982,2015]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Peromyscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="113" pageNumber="392" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="boylii">P. boylii</taxonomicName>
and most likely represents a cryptic species with subspecies 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1903" box="[2263,2340,2061,2094]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Peromyscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="113" pageNumber="392" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="beatae">beatae</taxonomicName>
and sacarensis. Two subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
